summary: My mother-in-law sent a message to the family group chat a few days ago that went something like this: “Hey, there’s still a few weeks left of summer and I think we should all play a long-distance game together.  Let’s all download a license plate tracker app, and compete to find the most state plates.  It’d be a good excuse to check in periodically so that I know you’re all still alive and well...
title: License Plate Game: Long-Distance Family Edition
